    </div>
   =20
    <div id=3D"div-gpt-ad-Programizcom36796" style=3D"margin: 32px 0; min-h=
eight: 250px;">
    </div>
    </div><div class=3D"clearfix"></div><p>Don't let the <code>struct node*=
* adjLists</code> overwhelm you.</p>

<p>All we are saying is we want to store a pointer to <code>struct node*</c=
ode>. This is because we don't know how many vertices the graph will have a=
nd so we cannot create an array of Linked Lists at compile time.</p>

<hr>
<h2 id=3D"cpp">Adjacency List C++</h2>

<p>It is the same structure but by using the in-built list STL data structu=
res of C++, we make the structure a bit cleaner. We are also able to abstra=
ct the details of the implementation.</p>

<pre style=3D"max-height: 600px;"><code class=3D"dsa hljs cpp"><span class=
=3D"hljs-class"><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-title">Graph</span>{</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">int</span> numVertices;
    <span class=3D"hljs-built_in">list</span>&lt;<span class=3D"hljs-keywor=
d">int</span>&gt; *adjLists;
   =20
  <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">public</span>:
    Graph(<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">int</span> V);
    <span class=3D"hljs-function"><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">void</span> =
<span class=3D"hljs-title">addEdge</span><span class=3D"hljs-params">(<span=
 class=3D"hljs-keyword">int</span> src, <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">int</s=
pan> dest)</span></span>;
};</code></pre>

<hr>
<h2 id=3D"java">Adjacency List Java</h2>

<p>We use Java Collections to store the Array of Linked Lists.</p>

<pre style=3D"max-height: 600px;"><code class=3D"dsa hljs cpp"><span class=
=3D"hljs-class"><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class=3D"hl=
js-title">Graph</span>{</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">private</span> <span class=3D"hljs-keyword=
">int</span> numVertices;
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">private</span> LinkedList&lt;integer&gt; a=
djLists[];
}</code></pre>

<p>The type of LinkedList is determined by what data you want to store in i=
t. For a labeled graph, you could store a dictionary instead of an Integer<=
/p>

<hr>
<h2 id=3D"python">Adjacency List Python</h2>

<p>There is a reason Python gets so much love. A simple dictionary of verti=
ces and its edges is a sufficient representation of a graph. You can make t=
he vertex itself as complex as you want.</p>

<pre style=3D"max-height: 600px;"><code class=3D"dsa hljs bash">graph =3D {=
<span class=3D"hljs-string">'A'</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-built_in">set</=
span>([<span class=3D"hljs-string">'B'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-string">=
'C'</span>]),
         <span class=3D"hljs-string">'B'</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-built_=
in">set</span>([<span class=3D"hljs-string">'A'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">'D'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-string">'E'</span>]),
         <span class=3D"hljs-string">'C'</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-built_=
in">set</span>([<span class=3D"hljs-string">'A'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs=
-string">'F'</span>]),
         <span class=3D"hljs-string">'D'</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-built_=
in">set</span>([<span class=3D"hljs-string">'B'</span>]),
         <span class=3D"hljs-string">'E'</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-built_=
in">set</span>([<span class=3D"hljs-string">'B'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs=
